      {
        "id": "5cf3ad5c4b95fcd8fadca11d6188b1b7ba1a1200",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2627,
          "name": "Abdelmuhaimen Seaudi",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "abdelmuhaimen.seaudi@orange.com",
          "username": "abdelseaudi"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-10-23 08:31:30.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWe are using similar structure like the python variant of this script, which is using NETCONF library that was built in CDS, and that is extending AbstractComponentFunction. If we don't extend NetconfComponentFunction in our script, we will have to write a big part of the impementation of NetconfComponentFunction, to run the methods:\n      nc.connect()\n      nc.lock()\n      nc.discard_change()\n      nc.edit_config() \n      nc.edit_config()  \n      nc.commit()\n      nc.unlock()      \n      nc.get_config()\t\t\t\t\n      nc.disconnect()",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "655c182e0c819ccda859edb6b6299e3cc1758656",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4357,
          "name": "Brinda Santh Muthuramalingam",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "brindasanth@in.ibm.com",
          "username": "brindasanthm"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-10-23 13:25:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> We are using similar structure like the python variant of this script, which is using NETCONF library that was built in CDS, and that is extending AbstractComponentFunction. If we don't extend NetconfComponentFunction in our script, we will have to write a big part of the impementation of NetconfComponentFunction, to run the methods:\n>       nc.connect()\n>       nc.lock()\n>       nc.discard_change()\n>       nc.edit_config() \n>       nc.edit_config()  \n>       nc.commit()\n>       nc.unlock()      \n>       nc.get_config()\t\t\t\t\n>       nc.disconnect()\n\nAbdelmuhaimen,\n\nThere are some standards to implement ComponentScripts, so that framework will call the script in generic way and user will implement in same way throughout the CDS. CDS has the extension function capability for all service functions (ie in this case NetconfExecutionExtensions.kt, ResourceResolutionExtensions.kt). It attaches the function directly to AbstractComponentFunction -> AbstracrComponentScriptFunction. \n\nBy your implementation, You can inherit only one Capability and you can't reuse the capabilities in script implementation.\n\nJust extend AbstracrComponentScriptFunction and call the extension function directly inside your code.\n\nPlease refer below extension functions for your implementation:\n\nfun AbstractComponentFunction.netconfDevice(requirementName: String): NetconfDevice\nfun AbstractComponentFunction.netconfDeviceInfo(requirementName: String): DeviceInfo\nsuspend fun AbstractComponentFunction.storedContentFromResolvedArtifactNB(resolutionKey:String, artifactName: String): String \nsuspend fun AbstractComponentFunction.contentFromResolvedArtifactNB(artifactPrefix: String): String",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
